"""Functional tests for tenant/role management routes (Task 16a).

Coverage (each route: unauthenticated → 401; authenticated-but-unauthorized → 403 or 404;
authorized → success):
- POST /tenants                              — 401, 403 (non-platform-admin), 201 (platform.admin)
- GET /tenants/{tenant_id}/members           — 401, 404 (non-member), 200
- POST /tenants/{tenant_id}/members          — 401, 404 (non-member), 403 (member w/o perm), 201
- DELETE /tenants/{tenant_id}/members/{id}   — 401, 404 (non-member), 403 (member w/o perm),
                                               204, 409 (last admin)
- POST /tenants/{tenant_id}/members/{id}/roles     — 401, 404 (non-member), 403 (member w/o perm), 204
- DELETE /tenants/{tenant_id}/members/{id}/roles/{r} — 401, 404 (non-member), 403 (member w/o perm),
                                                       204, 409 (last admin)

The probe app mounts all three routers (auth + tenants + roles) against a real
test control DB so guards, sessions, and memberships are exercised end-to-end.

Non-member tenant-scoped routes return 404 (not 403) by design — the membership
precondition inside ``guard`` runs before the permission check, so existence is
never leaked (A-F8).
"""

from __future__ import annotations

